The paper deals with linear programming decoding of linear block codes, which is a topic in information theory (cs.IT). The paper also proposes a new algorithm for generating parity inequalities, which involves linear algebraic transformations of the parity-check matrix, suggesting a connection to data structures (cs.DS) and distributed computing (cs.DC). The paper also discusses the performance of the proposed algorithm in terms of error-rate performance, which is a topic in machine learning (cs.LG) and signal processing (cs.SI).
